cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with image generation and compares its results with state-of-the-art baselines on CIFAR10, CelebA and ImageNet datasets. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper proposes a new deep generation paradigm inspired by vector graphics systems. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses auto-encoding framework and Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) to validate the viability of the proposed approach. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach to enhance artists and designers creativity potential. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with image generation and proposes a new architecture to generate images with a virtually infinite resolution.
